div.div: Commented on #5783 [Bug]: Zitadel not returning "returnUrl" in state property of token makes zitadel implementation with Blazor Webassembly difficult

Addition: I'd check what the spec defines. If state is an arbitrary field, it may be a good idea to implement this behavior in zitadel-net instead of doing something in zitadel itself. And while testing this, I found out that ZITADEL has some restrictive CSP (which makes sense, unless you use ZITADEL in an SPA): Refused to frame 'https://cas-fee-advanced-ocvdad.zitadel.cloud/' because an ancestor violates the following Content Security Policy directive: "frame-ancestors 'none'". It could not create the IFrame to check the authentication state which defeats the purpose of SPA authentication.

Alright :) I think overwriting the default remote state object could be a good idea. My guess is, that in the OIDC Spec, the state is an arbitrary field and not necessarily an object with the return url.
Commented on #491 How to use with Blazor WebAssembly

So, I managed to get it working (for the Auth part at least). You need to add the following return Url in ZITADEL to your redirect urls: https://localhost:5443/authentication/login-callback . Afterwards, the login & redirect works. However, after the redirect (when fetching the user profile), the following error appears: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Rendering.WebAssemblyRenderer[100] Unhandled exception rendering component: An exception occurred executing JS interop: The JSON value could not be converted to Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Authentication.RemoteAuthenticationState.
